        <profileDesc>
            <creation/>
            <abstract>
                <p>In spite of its title and inclusion in manuscript collections of and lists of malkǝʾ-hymns, it might rather be considered a "pseudo-malkǝʾ" as its stanzas do not salute body parts (as in a typical malkǝʾ) but rather other, abstract features (like its greatness [stanza 9], its honour [stanza 10], and its beauty [stanza 11]).</p>
            </abstract>
